Q1/ What is the difference between a synchronized method and a synchronized block?
Ans) 

	Synchronized method :
   =======================
   
   1) lock should be either class level or object level .
   2) Scope on entire functionality comparatively has greater scope .
   3) Performance is low .
   4) Waiting time is high .	
   
   Synchronized block :
  =======================
  
  1) Lock should be any level .
  2) Scope only limited to some statement ,comparatively has lesser scope .
  3) Performance high .
  4) Waiting time low .  
   